<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12113e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12113e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12113e"> 113(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> moufles on his / hands at work</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Un corbeau lui avait enlev&eacute; l&apos;une des moufles dont il prot&eacute;geait ses mains durant le travail; comme jadis saint Ki&eacute;ran, dans une circonstance analogue, il commanda au voleur de la lui rapporter et le voleur s&apos;ex&eacute;cuta, docile et empress&eacute;. <br><font color="green">[A crow took from him <mark>one of the gloves he used to protect his hands during work</mark>. Much as Saint Ciaran had done in a similar circumstance long ago, he ordered the thief to bring it back to him and the thief did so, obediently and eagerly.]</font> <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 38</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
